Guinea May Plant 10,000 Hectares of Cotton This Year, RTG Says

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-08-14T12:11:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/guinea-gets-70-million-from-african-development-bank-rtg-says.html
Guinea aims to plant 10,000 hectares
of cotton this year,  Radio Television Guineenne  said.  The West African nation will also extend to 40,000 hectares
plantations of oil palm trees and hevea from January 2012, the
Conakry-based, state-owned broadcaster cited president  Alpha Conde  as saying yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry at 
 ocamara@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
